tion in Philadelphia, HU offers bachelor&#8217;s, master&#8217;s, and even doctoral degrees. They also have certificate programs for those seeking focused training.<\/p>\n<p>With a strong emphasis on practical applications, HU boasts programs in engineering, computer science, and game design alongside more traditional options. They even have work-study programs for international students.<\/p>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2252\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-300x199.webp\" alt=\"day one cpt universities\" width=\"1077\" height=\"714\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-300x199.webp 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-1024x678.webp 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-768x509.webp 768w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-1536x1017.webp 1536w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/debby-hudson-asviIGR3CPE-unsplash-2048x1356.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1077px) 100vw, 1077px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>6. New England College<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: Henniker, New Hampshire<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $8-9K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.nec.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Nestled in Henniker, New Hampshire, <strong>New England College (NEC)<\/strong> boasts a rich history dating back to 1946. This private liberal arts college offers a blend of undergraduate and graduate programs, catering to over 5,000 students.<\/p>\n<p>NEC prides itself on experiential learning, allowing students to gain practical skills alongside theoretical knowledge. Their program options are diverse, with over 60 associate&#8217;s and bachelor&#8217;s degrees, over 20 master&#8217;s programs, and even a doctoral program.<\/p>\n<p>From business and art to science and education, NEC offers a well-rounded curriculum for students seeking a traditional liberal arts experience with a focus on real-world application.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>7. McDaniel College<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main Campus: Westminster, Maryland<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $12K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.mcdaniel.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Steeped in tradition since 1867, <strong>McDaniel College in Westminster<\/strong>, Maryland, offers a classic college experience and work-study programs for international students.<\/p>\n<p>Originally known as Western Maryland College, it boasts a close-knit community with a fierce dedication to its students&#8217; academic journeys.<\/p>\n<p>McDaniel College emphasizes undergraduate programs with a strong focus on the liberal arts. Their curriculum fosters well-rounded individuals with majors ranging from classics and English to biology and computer science.<\/p>\n<p>The average class size is small, allowing for personalized attention from professors, and their beautiful 160-acre campus offers a welcoming environment for students.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>8. Westcliff University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main Campus: Irvine, California<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $13K-$20K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.westcliff.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Westcliff University, another California school, joins the others by offering a program that lets international students work right away (CPT). Their focus, according to their website, is to prepare students globally for success through practical and innovative programs, both online and on campus.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>9. Monroe College<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main Campus: New York City<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $12-19K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.monroecollege.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Monroe College<\/strong> isn&#8217;t quite located in New York City itself, but it&#8217;s a great option for those seeking a college experience close by. Founded in 1933, Monroe College has campuses in the Bronx and New Rochelle, New York.<\/p>\n<p>They offer a variety of undergraduate and graduate programs with a focus on career-ready fields. Popular options include business, criminal justice, and human services. Monroe College prides itself on being affordable and offers opportunities for international students.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>10. California Institute of Advanced Management<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: Alhambra, California<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $12K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ciam.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Aiming to equip responsible business leaders, the <strong>California Institute of Advanced Management (CIAM)<\/strong> offers MBA programs in Project Management, Business Analytics, and Executive Management.<\/p>\n<p>This Alhambra, California-based nonprofit university emphasizes practical applications of management principles founded by Peter Drucker. CIAM keeps affordability in mind, making its MBA programs accessible to a wider range of students.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>11. Sofia University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: California<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $12K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.sofia.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Sofia University, with campuses in Palo Alto and Costa Mesa, California, is a unique option for work-study programs for international students.<\/p>\n<p>Founded in 1975, it originally focused on transpersonal psychology, exploring the full spectrum of human experience. Today, Sofia University offers undergraduate and graduate programs in various fields, including psychology and business, while still incorporating a transpersonal perspective.<\/p>\n<p>They cater to adult learners, typically those in their mid-20s to 60s, and promote a well-rounded approach to education that integrates intellectual, emotional, and spiritual aspects.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>12. Campbellsville University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: Campbellsville, Kentucky<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $10K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.campbellsville.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Campbellsville University (CU)<\/strong> is a private Christian university located in Campbellsville, Kentucky. Established in 1906, it has a long history of providing religious education.<\/p>\n<p>CU offers a variety of programs for all levels, from certificates and associate degrees to bachelor&#8217;s and master&#8217;s degrees. Their curriculum integrates faith with academics across various fields like business, education, and even nursing.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>13. Humphreys University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: California<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $9K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.humphreys.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Humphreys University<\/strong>, originally Humphreys College, is a non-profit university with over 120 years of experience providing education in California. They have campuses in Stockton and Modesto and offer a range of programs for both undergraduate and graduate students.<\/p>\n<p>These programs span various fields, including law, business, education, human services, and liberal arts, leading to certificates, associate&#8217;s degrees, bachelor&#8217;s degrees, master&#8217;s degrees, and even Juris Doctor degrees.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>14. Ottawa University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: Ottawa, Kansas<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $15-18K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ottawa.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Ottawa University (OU)<\/strong> is a university in Kansas with a long history dating back to 1865. Their main campus resides in Ottawa, Kansas.<\/p>\n<p>Still, they also have a residential campus in Surprise, Arizona, and additional locations focused on adult learners scattered across the Kansas City, Phoenix, and Milwaukee areas.<\/p>\n<p>OU offers a mix of undergraduate and graduate programs, with a focus on the fields of business and technology. Popular options include Kinesiology and Exercise Science, Biology, and Business Administration.<\/p>\n<p>They offer work-study programs for international students and emphasize a balance between academics and a vibrant campus life, with opportunities for athletics and extracurricular activities.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>15. International Technological University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: San Jose, California<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $14-23K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/itu.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>The International Technological University (ITU)<\/strong> is a California school founded in 1994. They offer undergraduate and graduate degrees in business and tech fields, like computer science and digital arts.<\/p>\n<p>ITU is involved in STEM education and helps students get internships through their Academic Internship Program. They even have a program that lets international students start working right away.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2251\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/medium-shot-colleagues-discussing-table-300x200.webp\" alt=\"work-study programs for international students\" width=\"1031\" height=\"688\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/medium-shot-colleagues-discussing-table-300x200.webp 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/medium-shot-colleagues-discussing-table-1024x683.webp 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/medium-shot-colleagues-discussing-table-768x512.webp 768w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/medium-shot-colleagues-discussing-table-1536x1024.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1031px) 100vw, 1031px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>16. Sullivan University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main campus: Louisville, Kentucky<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $16-19K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.sullivan.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Located in Kentucky with campuses in Louisville, Lexington, and Fort Knox, Sullivan University is a private for-profit institution established in 1962.<\/p>\n<p>They offer programs designed for quick career entry, with certificates and diplomas alongside traditional associate&#8217;s, bachelor&#8217;s, and even graduate degrees.<\/p>\n<p>The university focuses on career-oriented programs across various fields, including business, technology, and healthcare. They also cater to busy adults by providing flexible learning options, including online and hybrid formats.<\/p>\n<p>Students can potentially begin earning while they learn through Sullivan University&#8217;s day 1 CPT program for international students.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>17. National Louis University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main Campus: Chicago, Illinois<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $15K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/nl.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>National Louis University (NLU)<\/strong> is a private, non-profit university with a focus on adult learners. Founded in 1886, it boasts a long history in Chicago, Illinois, with a secondary campus in Tampa, Florida. NLU offers over 60 undergraduate and graduate programs across four colleges, catering to a diverse student body.<\/p>\n<p>Their programs range from education and human services to business and culinary arts, all designed to help students achieve their professional goals.<\/p>\n<p>NLU prides itself on its student-centered approach, providing features like personalized success coaches, work-study programs for international students and flexible learning options.<\/p>\n<p>if you want to know about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/free-universities-in-europe-2023\/\">Free universities in Europe<\/a> read this article:<\/p>\n<blockquo