my and has grown into a respected liberal arts college.<\/p>\n<p>St. Francis College offers a wide range of undergraduate programs, with 72 majors and minors across 19 academic departments. These include traditional liberal arts subjects alongside relevant fields like business administration, computer science, and digital arts.<\/p>\n<p>The college emphasizes a well-rounded education and boasts a strong focus on the American STEM Initiative, encouraging students in science, technology, engineering, and math. They even provide an Academic Internship Program to help students gain practical experience.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>20. American National University<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Main Campus: Roanoke, Virginia<\/li>\n<li>Tuition range: $21K\/year<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.an.edu\/\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>American National University (ANU)<\/strong> is a private, for-profit university with a focus on career-oriented programs. Established in 1886, it has a long history and offers degrees at multiple campuses across several states, including Tennessee, Virginia, and Kentucky.<\/p>\n<p>ANU caters to students seeking a quicker path to a job with programs ranging from associate degrees and diplomas to bachelor&#8217;s and even master&#8217;s degrees. They specialize in fields like healthcare, business, and information technology.<\/p>\n<p>Their website emphasizes features like low tuition, accelerated programs, and credit for life experiences, all designed to help students graduate faster and enter the workforce sooner.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Resources:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/day1cptuniversities.com\/day-1-cpt-universities\">https:\/\/day1cptuniversities.com\/day-1-cpt-universities<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.novacredit.com\/resources\/day-1-cpt-universities\">https:\/\/www.novacredit.com\/resources\/day-1-cpt-universities<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This Abroadin guide explores d